The paper focuses on improving machine reading comprehension models, which is a task commonly studied in natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning (ML) research. The use of multi-head self-attentive pooling and relation networks also suggests a focus on deep learning techniques, which are commonly used in computer vision (CV) and neural networks (NE) research. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), and cs.LG (Machine Learning), followed by cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) and cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
